By speaking several languages, including those of emerging economies, children will be given a better chance of finding rewarding employment.
In Scotland, each school will teach different languages.
Several of them will focus on classical contemporary languages, while others will teach languages that are important to the United Kingdom in 2020, including Mandarin or Japanese.
Whatever your child's preferences, several languages will be available in independent schools, with specialist staff in the field.
Scottish independent schools want to offer a learning environment that will prepare children and give them the skills necessary for their success, regardless of what future reserves them.
